    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "Like anyone else, I almost died young.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "It was summertime, trees golden-green.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 8
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "We were swimming at my my friend Mitchell Dotson’s grandmother’s house by a county road hidden on the other side of a hill.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "My mom and Mitchell's mom sat poolside, keeping a eye on us while chatting.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 7
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "Mitchell could swim in the deep end.<br><br><br>Katie and I were in the shallow end, but I wouldn’t stay there long.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 7
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "I remember walking down the ramp, the water creeping coldly up my chest, swallowing my collarbones and gulping my head.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "I saw the belly of the pool as if looking through a kaleidoscope of aqua-marine, everything dappled and fragmented in the summer sun.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "I realized I was drowning once I started wailing. The more I kept fighting the deeper I sank, the deeper the fear. I knew I was dying.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "But Laura Dotson saved me.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "She was five months pregnant.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "Laura dove into her mother’s pool and lifted me up while Holland spun in the pool of her mother’s womb.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "I remember the painful satisfaction of breathing again, my eyes closed.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "I remember slowly acclimating myself to the life buzzing and growing about me.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    },
    {
      "slide_title": "",
      "slide_text": "I am still drowning.",
      "bg_color": "white",
      "bg_image": "",
      "text_color": "black",
      "text_font": "Times New Roman",
      "text_size": "200%",
      "text_align": "center",
      "audio_file": "",
      "video_file": "",
      "slide_length": 5
    }
  ]
